  "prompt": "What is crawling in SEO?",
  "response": "In SEO (Search Engine Optimization), crawling is the process by which search engines like Google discover and scan websites to understand their content and structure. Here are key details about crawling:\n\n1. Definition\n- Crawling is when search engine bots (spiders or crawlers) systematically browse web pages\n- These automated bots follow links from one page to another, collecting information\n\n2. Purpose\n- Discover new and updated web pages\n- Index content for search engine results\n- Understand website structure and relationships between pages\n- Analyze website quality and relevance\n\n3. How Crawling Works\n- Search engine bots start with known webpages\n- Follow hyperlinks to discover new pages\n- Use algorithms to determine which pages to crawl and how frequently\n- Analyze page content, metadata, and technical elements\n\n4. Key Crawling Components\n- Robots.txt file (instructs crawlers which pages to crawl)\n- XML sitemaps (helps search engines understand website structure)\n- Internal linking\n- Website speed and accessibility\n\n5. Factors Affecting Crawling\n- Website architecture\n- Page load speed\n- Mobile-friendliness\n- Content quality\n- Number and quality of internal/external links\n\nEffective crawling helps search engines understand and rank web content accurately.",
